items.summary:
- *Milling chatter* causes severe vibrations, damaging surface quality, tools, and machines in high-value manufacturing.
- The study introduces *machine learning models*—including hybrid LSTM-FCN, GRU-FCN, and TCN—to predict and quantify chatter from *time-series vibration data*.
- The *GRU-FCN model* outperformed others, offering improved *accuracy*, *stability*, and real-time monitoring capabilities when milling parameters are included.

